description: Let G be an n-node graph with valencies d_1 .. d_n say; let m = (d_1+..+d_n)/n and s = n*Sum( (d_i-m)^2 ) be the scaled degree variance; a(n) gives number of different values taken by s.
references: Computed by Jan Hagberg, Dept. Statistics, Stockholm Univ., Sweden.
J. Hagberg, Centrality testing and the distribution of the degree variance in Bernoulli graphs Research report 2008:8(2000), Stockholm University, Department of Statistics.
links: J. Hagberg, Centrality testing and the distribution of the degree variance in Bernoulli graphs, Research Report 2000:8, Department of Statistics, Stockholm University, 2000.
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
extensions: Hagberg reference from C. Ronaldo (aga_new_ac(AT)hotmail.com), Dec 29 2004
